==English==
===Etymology===
From Hebrew ''dûnām'' or Arabic [[دونم]], from Turkish [[dönüm]], from [[dönmek]] ‘go round’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'dʊnəm/

===Noun===
'''dunam'''
# a measure of land in the Ottoman Empire and successive states, including Israel, where it corresponds to about 900 square [[metres]]